Benefits Administrator
Human Resource
0-5 years
Arizona - Phoenix



JOB DESCRIPTION
Education
High School Diploma
 
Experience
2 -5 years experience in an administrative role
 
Skills
Strong customer service and communication skills (written and verbal)
Strong attention to detail and accuracy
Must be able to maintain confidentiality
Strong PC & HRIS skills
Excellent organizational skills
 
General Responsibilities

Conduct new hire benefit orientation sessions to present overview of company benefit plans along with ensuring that new hires receive all the applicable benefit information;
Processing new hire initial enrollment in the system, and auditing the deductions prior to payroll processing for accuracy;
Coordinate COBRA subsidies with the third party administrator per severance agreements;
Administer Leaves of Absence working with employees and the third party administrator in accordance with all State/Federal laws and in compliance with Company policies;
Help to coordinate annual open enrollment process for benefit plans and wellness fairs;
Respond to and resolve employee questions and issues related to benefits or providers, serve as liaison between employees and providers;
Audit and coordinate reconciliation of invoices and timely payment to providers along with setup of new providers in the system;
Manage Education Assistance, Fitness Reimbursement, and Way of Wellness programs;
Update applicable employee communication and forms as needed;
Process and collect applicable forms for all Life Events;
Process benefit terminations in the payroll system as needed;
Provide manual reports to FMLA administrator, telemedicine provider, and international travel carrier;
Work with carriers to resolve errors on weekly EDI files.


