Senior Electrical Engineer II
Engineering / R＆D
0-5 years
Arizona - Phoenix



JOB DESCRIPTION
You will provide solutions to problems of low/medium complexity associated with specific projects. Contribute towards the achievement of milestones associated with specific projects. Must possess the ability to work on assignments of low/medium complexity under some supervision and guidance of a senior engineer.
 

Integrate lower level sub-assemblies to obtain desired system level configuration.
	 

Create a fail safe system level electrical designs including signal distribution, interlock systems, and some printed wiring board designs maintaining code compliance and product design safety criteria.
	 

Create, check, review and analyze schematics, assembly drawings, test procedures, and equipment performance specifications.
	 

Evaluate engineering change orders and implement changes following established procedures and schedules.
	 

Prepare product/system design and associated documentation for the manufacture and testing of products manufactured by ASM. The documentation shall be complete, easy to follow and depict a level of accuracy surpassing the customers’ (internal and external) expectations.
	 

Support and provide a test set up for testing of hardware for cost reduction and product enhancement projects. Design and build test fixtures, support basic instrumentation with hardware, perform electro-mechanical tests as required and maintain reliability data and records of all evaluations performed.
	 

Provide engineering support to manufacturing and test groups to resolve design related issues.
	 

Support field service groups in defining and implementing solutions for problems encountered in the field.
	 

Design test fixtures for performance evaluation of new designs before their incorporation into the standard product structure.
	 

Review technical manuals and update tech pubs on revised documentation needs.
	 

Provide electrical system integration, interfacing and interconnect for products manufactured by ASM.
	 

Support document control in establishing relevant procedures for the manufacture of different sub assemblies like cable assemblies, PCB assemblies, and wiring diagrams, etc.

 
Experience

2 - 5 years of experience in the design of logic circuits, equipment controls, and systems integration.
Should be familiar with documentation procedures as established in a manufacturing environment or an equivalent combination of education and experience for which comparable knowledge, skills, and ability.

 
Skills

Should be proficient in the design, documentation and debug of control systems involving digital and analog circuits. Demonstrated proficiency in circuit and circuit board design.
A good grasp of digital & analog control theory is essential.
Some familiarity with national/international standards applicable to electrical systems is desirable.
Computer background in Microsoft applications (Excel, Word), inventory management (MRP) and AutoCAD 2011 is desirable.
	 


Education

BS degree in electrical engineering
Some background courses in semiconductor device manufacturing desirable.


Apply now



Manager Platform Engineering
Engineering / R＆D
+10 years
Arizona - Phoenix



JOB DESCRIPTION
Education
 
MS degree in mechanical engineering or related degree(s) preferred.
 
 Experience
 

Ten years of experience in the engineering and design of complex mechanical systems including: motion controls, gas, pneumatics, water, and vacuum systems, handling systems, and product packaging.
Five years of management in the semiconductor industry
Minimum five years of technical/engineering management experience.
	 


 Skills  
 

Semiconductor capital equipment experience is required
Demonstrated experience in design, development and integration of system level mechanical features and functions, including configuration control aspects.
Able to direct/work with a diverse group of people to achieve requirements and specifications on complex projects.
Knowledgeable in the requirements for CE, NFPA, OSHA, Semi S2/S8/S22/F47 and other relevant standards as applicable to semiconductor manufacturing equipment.
Ability to create, check, review and analyze mechanical and electrical designs, test procedures and equipment specifications.
Capability to manage resource schedules/planning/coordinating and reporting activities. This includes interfacing with other organizations and outside vendors.
Effective verbal and written communications skills.
Ability to present design concepts to management and peers in a professional and effective manner.
Ability to work in a team environment with aggressive deadlines and multiple priorities while maintaining a team player attitude.
Self-confident yet humble, with a high degree of integrity.
An intense desire for success, with an ability to learn and improve from past mistakes
Strong technical management skills
Strong team motivation and leadership skills
Understanding of materials: metals, plastics, quartz, heat transfer, surface coatings and surface finishes.
Computer background in Microsoft applications Pro/ENGINEER, ANSYS and AutoCAD.
Knowledge of mechanical design and drafting best practices and ANSI Y14.5, including geometric tolerances

           
 General Job Description
 

Lead Hardware Engineering (mechanical, electrical, systems) team responsible for developing and/or making improvements to semiconductor manufacturing equipment.
Demonstrated subject matter expertise by managing the creation and execution of continuous improvement projects to enhance the reliability and lower the cost of existing platform systems.
Provide technical guidance to team, manage resource loading, and maintaining schedules for all engineering projects.
Drive engineering projects from conception through engineering release utilizing ECO release processes.
Represent the engineering team on technical projects and programs. Regularly, prepare and deliver technical project presentations and status to management and directly to customers
Exhibit a self-starter personality with the ability to take on a wide range of technically challenging projects.
Review and create internal technical specifications, customer technical specifications, industry standards and regulations/standards.
Evaluate engineering calculations and designs for mechanical, stress, thermal, mechanical, tolerances and fluid dynamics problems.
Set group and individual goals and objectives, and periodically review performance vs objectives.
Work with a global, cross-functional team utilizing excellent communication skills, including traveling to represent the team in global meetings.
Travel to customer sites to participate in technical discussions.
Interface with other organizations on new product updates, and ensure a smooth transition of the product into the manufacturing cycle.

 
 
Job Complexities
 
Perform self-inspection of all work, and is responsible for ensuring that all work performed adheres to documentation requirements, company policies and procedures.
 
May be exposed to following hazardous materials used or exposed to hazardous environments while performing duties: loud noises, metal/moving objects, flammable/toxic/corrosive materials, hot surfaces, lasers, infrared radiation, electrical/pneumatic (pressurized) circuits and adhesives. This will require that employee wear eye, hearing and hand protection as needed to protect themselves from exposure. These will be supplied upon request.
 
This position may require cleanroom apparel and safety equipment. This work normally requires extended periods of standing, setting and occasional lifting of up to 50 pounds.

