Senior Field Process Engineer II
Engineering / R＆D
0-5 years
Arizona - Phoenix



JOB DESCRIPTION
Senior Process Development Engineer - Key Account
(This position will be based in Boise, ID)
 
ASM International N.V. is a leading supplier of semiconductor process equipment. The Company possesses a strong technological base, state-of-the-art manufacturing facilities, a competent and qualified workforce and a highly trained, strategically distributed support network worldwide.  As a member of the Key-Account organization of the Global Sales and Services business unit, the Key Account Process Development engineer is the on-site process application expert to expand opportunities on ASM’s installed products. In this role, he/she is driving the process development projects and is the bridge between the customer process development teams and the business unit. During the transfer of the technology to the production fabs, the process engineer will ensure all the best-known-methods (BKM’s) are transferred ensuring a smooth transition. In case of systems down situations, you will work in the escalation process with the local FSE team to solve the problem as soon as possible. 
 
Main tasks of a Process Development Engineer
On site process development

Analyze current baseline process performance, identify gaps with respect to next technology node requirements
Perform problem and root cause analysis of system performance issues (non-conformances) at customer sites.
Drive development of structural solutions, set engineering requirements.
Customer JDP or Site Beta Transfer Work
Develop solutions in close cooperation with R&D and Process Development.
Test and qualify new solutions at the customer site

 
New Product Introduction (NPI), ramp to HVM production

Assist in process transfer to HVM fabs
Ensure transfer of product knowledge (training) to local service organizations
Document BKM’s

 
Escalation management

Pro-actively support escalations, develop and manage action plans.
Ensure clear communication between customer, on-site service crew, R&D, and suppliers.

 
Education/Experience requirements

Master/Bachelors degree (or equivalent) in Physics, Chemical Engineering, Material Science or similiar.
>4 years relevant experience within (international) service organization.
Strong experience with advanced troubleshooting/problem analysis methodologies (KT/FMEA/7-step/…).
Good knowledge of semiconductor device applications, vacuum technique, and PEALD/ALD/PECVD deposition processes, preferably with the XP-8 PEALD technology
Interacts directly with customers to achieve customer satisfaction.

 
Competencies

Excellent international communication skills.
Customer-oriented.
Pro-active, goal-oriented, driver mentality.
Team player
Flexibility, willingness to travel abroad

 
Career Opportunities
Due to the international nature of this function you can develop yourself as a technical expert with excellent communication and management skills. Within this job you are involved in many ASM departments. This will create an excellent steppingstone for further career opportunities at ASM, like (R&D) Management, Project Management, and Technical Account Management.

Apply now



Product Marketing Manager
Marketing ＆ Business Development
5-10 years
Arizona - Phoenix



JOB DESCRIPTION
As a Product Marketing Manager, you will work closely with a variety of business functions ranging from Business Development, Sales, Finance, Operations and Technology & Engineering Teams and coordinate execution across these functional groups. The Product Manager role is among the most challenging and rewarding. We are looking for a highly talented and driven individual who is excited to take on this challenge.
 
Focus on continuously improving your product and delivering new consumer-focused solutions to create additional value for our customers. You will leverage consumer insights, market needs and go-to-market strategy to fine-tune your offering. In addition, you will define and evaluate new product offerings, coordinate cross-functional market launches, define success metrics, diligently track key metrics and improve new products over time

DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES

• Owns products end to end from strategy to execution and has a mission to make his/her product the best in the industry, improving value for ASM and our customers
• Responsible for driving new product launches collaborating with a wide range of functional groups
• Diligently manages products using metrics driven approach and continuously drives improvement in these metrics
• Leads various qualitative and quantitative customer research to better understand customer perspectives and refine insights
• Serves as the champion of ASM customers, understands their needs/aspirations in detail through qualitative and quantitative means and uses the insight to actively improve our products
• Evangelizes product, strategy and roadmap with various functional groups across ASM (particularly with sales) and drive excitement
• Ensures messaging of key product features, processes, expectations, performance, etc. is accurate, clear, and delivered consistently across departments
• Stays up to date on changes to our industry and business processes, identify impact of changes on all processes, materials, and messaging, and work with departments to ensure changes are absorbed


Qualifications Desired:
• Experience as a process engineer or hardware engineer in the semicap industry.
• 7 or more years of experience in Product Management and related disciplines, preferably in a world class tech company/start up.
• Experience developing, executing, and owning best-in-class products desired
• Demonstrated excellence in qualitative empathy driven customer research, rigorous data based analysis, business case building
• Semi cap industry experience and understanding desired but not required.  An undergraduate technical degree is required. PhD is preferred.
 
SKILL REQUIREMENTS
Competencies

• High Standards: expects personal performance and team performance to be nothing short of the best 
• Customer Obsession: has high degree of customer empathy and drive to understand customers; uses insight to guide product priorities
• Product and business judgment: has the judgment to prioritize best product improvements and deliver great end to end customer experience based on customer and market need, organizational limitations and business environment
• Process Management: can lead complex end to end processes with stakeholders across functional groups and several interdependencies
• Analytical skills: can build robust models and analyze vast quantities of data to unearth most important insights; Excel capabilities required
• Learning and continuous improvement mindset: actively solicits feedback to improve self; proactive about improving product by always generating hypotheses and validating hypotheses
• Attention to detail: pays attention to the specifics, in terms of process, customer experience or detailed metrics to deliver on product outcomes
• Communication: listens for meaning, translates concepts effectively and is articulate with both verbal and written communication; can command a room full of business leaders and drive outcomes
• Adaptability: adjusts quickly to changing priorities and conditions; anticipates and copes effectively with the complexity of change 

PHYSICAL DEMANDS:
• Able to listen and communicate verbally 
• Able to travel up to 50% of time
 

Apply now



Staff Global Product Support Engineer
Engineering / R＆D
5-10 years
Arizona - Phoenix



JOB DESCRIPTION
ASM America is currently seeking Global Product Support (GPS) Engineer for our Phoenix, AZ office.
 
Key Responsibilities 
 

System level expert focused on product support for new product development.    
Interaction with Hardware, Electrical, Controls, Process, and Software engineering teams to become the system level expert on new products being developed.
Provides guidance to engineering during the design phase of new products on key customer requirements and needs.  Including PM service tasks, design for service, design for manufacturability, etc.
Owns first build and test of the new product in the development lab, working closely with engineering teams providing real time feedback of issues and recommends solutions.
Develops procedures and documents best known methods for service, preventive and corrective maintenance tasks
Owns First in Fab (Alpha or Beta) customer shipments.   Drives customer fab readiness (facilities set up), installation and start up through production qualification.
Detailed Reporting of field issues for new products in the field
Drives and owns customer issues on new products during the Alpha build and test phase as well as during beta testing at customer sites.  
Develops critical spares parts lists for new products, ensures initial stocking levels are set and ready for new product shipments

 
Travel
 

Depending on the product development cycle. Ranges from 25% to 75%

 
Education 
 

Bachelor's Degree in engineering discipline
