Skills
 
Requires strong procedural and math skills. Good understanding of ASME Y14.5 (Dimensioning and Tolerancing), capable of product tolerance studies. Strong understanding of manufacturing processes, procedures, materials and techniques, including manufacturability concerns for each part designed.  The ability to read and understand difficult instructions and maintain written  records is essential.  Excellent functional understanding of AutoCAD and Pro/ENGINEER software.
 
General Job Description
 
Responsible for designing and detailing the documentation required for the manufacture of ASM America products, preparing complete production detail drawings and contributing design modifications to improve the quality of products and/or facilitate manufacturing operations. Involves computer aided drafting of mechanical and electrical sub-assemblies with complex parts using Pro/ENGINEER software on a PC based computer system, with the highest degree of accuracy, cost-effectiveness and with the highest quality of design.
 

Ensure completeness of documentation for mechanical/electrical assemblies, electrical and pneumatic schematics, wiring diagrams for the manufacture of ASM products.
	 

