Senior Facilities Engineer
Engineering / R＆D
5-10 years
Arizona - Phoenix



JOB DESCRIPTION
Education
 
Bachelor’s Degree in an Engineering (or related) discipline highly preferred. High school degree or equivalent required.
 
Experience
 
Minimum of 5 years experience in the design of electro-mechanical systems, with 2 - 4 years actual working experience with Pro-Engineering software. Requires specific experience relative to company's immediate needs in either mechanical design, electrical design, E/M design or design checking or an equivalent combination of education and experience for which comparable knowledge, skills and ability has been achieved.
 
Skills
 
Solid understanding of ANSI Y14.5 (Dimensioning and Tolerancing), capable of product tolerance studies. Strong understanding of manufacturing processes, procedures, materials and techniques, including manufacturability concerns for each part designed.  Requires strong procedural and math (algebra, geometry and trigonometry) skills. The ability to read and understand difficult instructions and  maintain  written  records  is  essential.  Excellent functional understanding of AutoCAD and Pro-Engineering software.
 
General Job Description
 
As the support representative of the equipment lab and facilities manager and organization, the Facilities Engineer facilitates advanced projects and programs. Executes project leadership role and aids the development of technical ideas into final product by providing guidance and coordinating the efforts of a diverse group of technical professionals. Must be highly motivated with ability to take on complex assignments with minimal or no direction.
 
 
Key Responsibilities 
•   Apply sound engineering and business principles, equipment/product specifications and research data to provide equipment and facilities to support development and applications tool sets for semiconductor industry.
•   Determine feasibility of product proposals, resolve problems based on technical inputs, business goals and develop new designs based on the same when requested, maintaining product design safety criteria.
•   Lead facility design reviews (30/60/90) with engineering teams to ensure facilities requirements and scope of work is clearly identified and comprehended.
•   Generate Scope of Work and Request for Quotations for all facility related projects. Work with contractors to obtain multiple quotes and choose optimal contact for ASM business needs.
 
•   Develop project micro-schedule and manage project/s to meet required timeline. Meet with contractors on daily basis to monitor progress, identify roadblocks and remove blocks when required.
•   Maintain protocol policies and procedures, upkeep, good housekeeping and controls for Class 1, 10, 100, 1000 and 10,000 Cleanrooms.  This includes all garments and consumable supplies to run and maintain clean environment.
•   Provide direction, procedures, means and ways for semiconductor fabrication equipment and it’s support equipment, related to various abatement, chemical and gas delivery, metrology, chilled water/DI water, waste water systems, vacuum, wet clean systems. This includes budget controls, cost reductions, cost estimates, generation of purchase orders.
•   Provide support to EHS department on EHS upgrades and defined projects and task as assigned.
•   Provide and maintain facilities security and life safety systems.
•   Provide and maintain all building facilities equipment and systems to maintain comfortable living quarters for all ASMA employees. This also includes internal relocations, furniture, and restroom and breakroom facilities and upkeep.  This includes but not limited to blanket orders and contracts for suppliers, purchase order spread sheet, cost transfers, and cost controls/reductions.
•   Provide support to various operation areas to maintain production requirements and productivity.
•   Provide leadership and engineering direction in finalization of specifications, designs, fabrication techniques and test protocols. This entails report generation, schedule creation and maintenance, design reviews and extensive inter departmental coordination. This also includes preparation of facilities cost spread sheet, WA, CAPX and contractor work scopes, project scheduling / planning (MPP) and reporting.
•   Instill teamwork, satisfy internal customer requirements and maintain schedules while following budgetary guidelines and constraints.
•   Hold and participate in design reviews for unique internal customer driven programs, for changes implementing product enhancements and other new designs prior to and during their development and installation.
•   Develop cost reduction projects and equipment improvement projects in conjunction with technical staff, managers and manufacturing groups. Support development and testing of associated hardware to verify performance objectives. Create test plans, verify and approve test procedures, and develop and maintain reliability data and records on all evaluations performed.

