Field Process Engineer
Customer Service
0-5 years
New York - Albany



JOB DESCRIPTION
Senior Process Development Engineer - Key Account
(This position will be based in Malta, NY)
 
ASM International N.V. is a leading supplier of semiconductor process equipment. The Company possesses a strong technological base, state-of-the-art manufacturing facilities, a competent and qualified workforce and a highly trained, strategically distributed support network worldwide.  As a member of the Key-Account organization of the Global Sales and Services business unit, the Key Account Process Development engineer is the on-site process application expert to expand opportunities on ASM’s installed products. In this role, he/she is driving the process development projects and is the bridge between the customer process development teams and the business unit. During the transfer of the technology to the production fabs, the process engineer will ensure all the best-known-methods (BKM’s) are transferred ensuring a smooth transition. In case of systems down situations, you will work in the escalation process with the local FSE team to solve the problem as soon as possible. 
 
Main tasks of a Process Development Engineer
On site process development

Analyze current baseline process performance, identify gaps with respect to next technology node requirements
Perform problem and root cause analysis of system performance issues (non-conformances) at customer sites.
Drive development of structural solutions, set engineering requirements.
Customer JDP or Site Beta Transfer Work
Develop solutions in close cooperation with R&D and Process Development.
Test and qualify new solutions at the customer site

 
New Product Introduction (NPI), ramp to HVM production

Assist in process transfer to HVM fabs
Ensure transfer of product knowledge (training) to local service organizations
Document BKM’s

 
Escalation management

Pro-actively support escalations, develop and manage action plans.
Ensure clear communication between customer, on-site service crew, R&D, and suppliers.

 
Education/Experience requirements

Master/Bachelors degree (or equivalent) in Physics, Chemical Engineering, Material Science or similiar.
>4 years relevant experience within (international) service organization.
Strong experience with advanced troubleshooting/problem analysis methodologies (KT/FMEA/7-step/…).
Good knowledge of semiconductor device applications, vacuum technique, and PEALD/ALD/PECVD deposition processes, preferably with the XP-8 PEALD technology
Interacts directly with customers to achieve customer satisfaction.

 
Competencies

Excellent international communication skills.
Customer-oriented.
Pro-active, goal-oriented, driver mentality.
Team player
Flexibility, willingness to travel abroad

 
Career Opportunities
Due to the international nature of this function you can develop yourself as a technical expert with excellent communication and management skills. Within this job you are involved in many ASM departments. This will create an excellent steppingstone for further career opportunities at ASM, like (R&D) Management, Project Management, and Technical Account Management.

Apply now



Senior Technical Support Engineer II
Customer Service
5-10 years
Arizona - Phoenix



JOB DESCRIPTION
Job Summary
An ASM equipment expert supporting GSS interest globally by providing support plus solutions to field and customer personnel by remote problem diagnosis. Lead and manage the escalation process / team as the organizations escalation owner while mentoring co-workers. Ability to resolve 90% of issues.
Provide value, teamwork and specific data through ASM existing SOP’s to drive FSE efficiency, improve global tool performance, and provide solutions and BKM’s.
Education
Bachelor's degree in a technical field (i.e. Engineering, Chemistry, Computer Science) or equivalent technical training.
OR
Associate's degree in technical field or equivalent technical training, and 8 years fab experience.
 
Experience
7 - 10 year’s experience in the electronic or semiconductor industry; 4 year’s experience at ASM or directly related experience. (i.e. ALD, PECVD, Epi, CVD, Diffusion)
 
Skills

Ability to handle all customer situations, developing action plans then

present and drive resolution to both ASM and customer.

Ability to rectify a bad situation and gain customer confidence
Strong positive attitude, ability to work in a team environment and work alone and drive meetings, provide guidance to co-workers, excellent internal ASM relations
Solid logical and Troubleshooting skills, able to teach co-workers
Ability to work responsibly with all ASM resources and departments in a multifunctional high paced atmosphere independent of supervision on highly complex problems
Ability to handle multiple tasks simultaneously and be able to organize and run a meeting
Be a system expert for support of field problems, travel to customer site domestically and internationally
Very highly skilled in electrical and mechanical techniques and overall equipment system knowledge (HW / SW, Process)
Strong computer skills, working knowledge of MS Word, Excel, OneComm, SharePoint, Sap
Drive ASM SOP’s and protocol, able to guide co-workers
	
Includes; PCP, PDP, change request, NC, CIP, clear technical input in CCB


Ability to handle 95% of support calls and escalations without assistance
Become an active member of ASM GSS core teams
Drive and execute knowledge of ASM Escalation process including managing action lists, handle 95% of support calls and legacy tool escalations without assistance.
Strong ability to develop action plans on technical issues with customers and field personnel and able to influence others to achieve results
Highly evolved phone and technical skills to analyze, technically direct and address tool issues remotely
Strong knowledge of Semiconductor vacuum techniques and troubleshooting
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills; speak and write in a clear concise manner. Accurately convey issues to peers, management, or customers.
Strong presentation skills
Strong organizational skills and leadership qualities
Accurate, timely reporting, ability to coach peers
Acts as a role model and mentor while assisting in the development of customer service skills with subordinates and peers
 

 
Essential Functions

Work in a safety-first mentality
Drive ASM process protocol (OneComm) with emphasis on Escalation to customers and peers and regularly institute or update service solutions to the field
Manage complex cross-functional projects globally
Consistently provide fast, quality solutions to field and customer personnel and create new BKM’s
Lead, manage and teach problem solving and root cause analysis
Strong ability to explain highly technical and complex information to peers, management and customers both in verbal or written mediums
Demonstrate highly evolved phone and computer skills that allow quick and efficient troubleshooting remotely
Exercise good judgment within broadly defined practices and policies in selecting methods, techniques, tools and evaluation criteria for obtaining desired results
Be willing to travel domestically and internationally as required, typically 30-40%
Drive Field Introduction Plans (FIP) and Site Specific Implementations Plans (SSIP) to support successful Field Operations with New Products.

 

