Instrumentation and Controls Specialist
Other
5-10 years
Arizona - Phoenix



JOB DESCRIPTION
Job Duties and Responsibilities

Oversee installation of Building controls system including but not limited to gas life safety, fire life safety, building management system of cleanrooms (T&H), water systems (Flow and pressure), scrubber and general exhaust system pressure and balance, building lighting. 
Must be an expert in gas life safety sensors and programming.
Must have design and construction management experience to oversee the new building controls system.
Must have understanding of all equipment that supports the lab and the building.
Support Operations and Facilities in their day to day activities.
Facilitate implementation of a preventative maintenance culture.
Continuously improve facilities organization capabilities to achieve best in class reliability.
Support the implementation of a comprehensive technical and behavioral culture.

 
 
Education and Experience

BS Degree in Instrumentation and Controls Engineering required. Associate degree with considerable experience in the area of responsibility may also be considered.
5+ years of experience as Maintenance or Reliability Engineer responsible for process instrumentation and controls.
Project Engineering and Maintenance Supervision experience is a plus.
Strong engineering skills with a thorough knowledge of instrumentation and controls engineering, this will include a distributed controls systems.
Knowledge of instrumentation standards as applied in semiconductor industry.
Experience in project cost and schedule control practices is a plus.


